description.narrative:
- Providing free legal assistance on civil cases, assisting refugees in obtaining Proof of Registration cards and providing other information services including on areas of intended return and referring vulnerable cases to UNHCR and other NGOs for other related services;
- Enhancing capacity of the legal practitioners (both formal and informal justice), police, judges, beneficiaries and other relevant stakeholders through training to address structural and bureaucratic impediments in accessing rights;
- Establishment of Basic Health Units, recruitment and capacity building of medical staff to ensure that emergency lifesaving health assistance is available to Afghan refugees in designated refugee camps;
- Provision of emergency reproductive health services to conduct deliveries and antenatal and post-natal consultations;
- Health awareness and hygiene promotion sessions in refugee camps, schools etc.
